text: Let G = (V,E) and G’ = (V, E') be two undirected graphs with the same set of nodes. G and G' are isomorphic if there is a permutation 7 of the nodes of G such that (i, j) is an edge of E if and only if (m(i),7(j)) is an edge of E'.
